**`process.env.NODE_ENV` restore is incorrect when `originalEnv` is `undefined`.**

When `NODE_ENV` was not previously set, `originalEnv` is `undefined`. Assigning `process.env.NODE_ENV = undefined` sets it to the **string** `"undefined"`, not deleting it. This can leak into subsequent tests.


<details>
<summary>üîß Proposed fix</summary>

```diff
-        process.env.NODE_ENV = originalEnv;
+        if (originalEnv === undefined) {
+          delete process.env.NODE_ENV;
+        } else {
+          process.env.NODE_ENV = originalEnv;
+        }
```

Alternatively, wrap the restore in a `finally` block for robustness:

```diff
+        try {
           await execute(interaction);
           const content = mockReply.mock.calls[0][0].content;
           expect(content).toContain('An internal error occurred.');
           expect(content).not.toContain('pg: connection refused');
-
-        process.env.NODE_ENV = originalEnv;
+        } finally {
+          if (originalEnv === undefined) {
+            delete process.env.NODE_ENV;
+          } else {
+            process.env.NODE_ENV = originalEnv;
+          }
+        }
```
</details>

